.:: Puzzle 4x5-Level-2-3::.
The people use 5 different means of transport: snowmobile, tram, van, taxi, bike
5 different games are played: whist, chess, domino, monopoly, billiard
The people grow 5 different varities of flowers: aconite, bellflower, rose, begonia, daisy
The people's birthday is in 5 different months: october, december, april, june, march
 1. the person driving the bike is the person who growsbellflower##1
 2. the person who's birthday is in june is in the middle##1
 3. the person who growsbegonia is in the middle##1
 4. the person playing whist is in the middle##1
 5. the person driving the bike is on the right of the person who's birthday is in december##1
 6. the person driving the tram is on the left of the person who growsaconite##1
 7. the person who growsdaisy is on the left of the person who's birthday is in april##1
 8. the person playing whist is on the right of the person playing chess##1
 9. the person who growsrose is on the far left##1
10. the person who's birthday is in october is the person playing monopoly##1
11. the person driving the van is on the right of the person who's birthday is in march##1
12. the person driving the taxi is on the right of the person who growsdaisy##1
13. the person who's birthday is in march is between the person playing billiard and the person driving the van##2

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1      |      2      |     3     |      4       |       5       |
| Transport         | snowmobile | bike     | van   | tram   | taxi |
| Game   | billiard  | chess | whist | monopoly | domino        |
| Flower   | rose      | bellflower      | begonia       | daisy       | aconite       |
| Birthday         | december | march  | june    | october    | april        |

